On the other hand, reducing government spending can have the opposite effect. It takes money out of the economy, which might lead to decreased demand and potentially higher unemployment.

Now, regarding taxation. When taxes are cut, individuals and businesses have more disposable income, which they can spend or invest. This increased spending also boosts demand and can stimulate economic growth. Conversely, raising taxes reduces disposable income, which can dampen spending and investment.

